Uses of Package
rules

  • Packages that use rules 
    Package Description
    board
    Contains classes describing items on a printed circuit board and the board itself.
    designformats.specctra
    Contains classes for reading and writing board designs in the Specctra dsn text format.
    gui
    Contains functionality of the graphical user interface based on javax.swing.
    interactive
    Contains functionality for interactive board handling, which is independent of the graphical user interface.
    rules
    Contains rules and restrictions for the items on a printed circuit board.
  • Classes in rules used by board 
    Class and Description
    BoardRules
    Contains the rules and constraints required for items to be inserted into a routing board
    ViaInfo
    Information about a combination of via_padstack, via clearance class and drill_to_smd_allowed used in interactive and automatic routing.
  • Classes in rules used by designformats.specctra 
    Class and Description
    BoardRules
    Contains the rules and constraints required for items to be inserted into a routing board
    Net
    Describes properties for an individual electrical net.
    NetClass
    Describes routing rules for individual nets.
  • Classes in rules used by gui 
    Class and Description
    ClearanceMatrix
    NxN Matrix describing the spacing restrictions between N clearance classes on a fixed set of layers.
    ViaInfos
    Contains the lists of different ViaInfo's, which can be used in interactive and automatic routing.
    ViaRule
    Contains an array of vias used for routing.
